HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 90
By Boyd
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Melanie R. Bean for her
honorable and astute service to the people of
Tennessee as the 2024–2025 president of the
Tennessee Association of Criminal Defense
Lawyers.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy individual is Melanie R. Bean of Lebanon, who is the
2024–2025 president of the Tennessee Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers (TACDL); and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers was formed and
chartered in 1973, making it the oldest legal defense bar association in the State; TACDL
provides education, training, and support to criminal defense lawyers and advocates for fair and
effective criminal justice in the courts and wherever justice demands; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Bean entered the world of criminal defense in 1998 when she served as
a law clerk for the Honorable Frank Lannom, whom she later joined in practice, and she has
been a member of TACDL for over twenty years; and
WHEREAS, no stranger to leadership, she has served two times on the TACDL Board of
Directors, a testament to her consistent devotion and the respect she has earned from her
peers; and
WHEREAS, a former legislative committee chair, Ms. Bean has regularly represented
TACDL in their legislative aims, including collaborating with legislators on policy development
and providing testimony to various committees in the legislature; and
