WHEREAS, Ms. Bean is equally active and influential outside of TACDL; she currently
serves as an appointed member of the Domestic Violence State Coordinating Counsel and
previously served as an appointed hearing committee member for the Tennessee Board of
Professional Responsibility from 2011 to 2017; and
WHEREAS, thanks to her superlative work and skill, she has rightfully accrued several
recognitions and honors, including the Workhouse Award and Rob W. Ritchie Award, both from
TACDL, as well as the Distinguished Alumni Award from Cumberland University; and
WHEREAS, apart from her work as a partner of Lannom and Williams, PLLC, Ms. Bean
helps to maintain her family's farm in Clay County on which she grew up; although she still
maintains a great love for her roots in Clay County, she now resides in Lebanon, where she is a
church member of The Bridge Fellowship; and
WHEREAS, her remarkable success in and outside of the courtroom stems from her
dedication to safeguarding basic human dignity and to serving others with her legal talents and
community involvement; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Bean has demonstrated the utmost professionalism, ability, and
integrity as an attorney and civic leader, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of
members of the bar and bench and her community alike; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Melanie R. Bean for her meritorious service to the
people of Tennessee as the 2024–2025 president of the Tennessee Association of Criminal
Defense Lawyers and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
